# ssm_regimes

Regime-model extensions to [lindermanlab/ssm](https://github.com/lindermanlab/ssm).

Provides uniform fit wrappers and causal filters for rSLDS, HMM, and AR-HMM
models, a restricted-EM variant of rSLDS, a SPRT-optimal CUSUM overlay for
regime-change detection, and generic regime-evaluation utilities.
Domain-agnostic.

## Installation

```bash
pip install git+https://github.com/chrismader1/ssm_regimes.git
```

Pulls `ssm` from the Linderman lab repo automatically.

## Public API

```python
from ssm_regimes import (
    # Fit wrappers (uniform signature across model families)
    fit_rSLDS, fit_rSLDS_restricted, fit_HMM, fit_AR_HMM,

    # Causal (forward-only) inference
    inference_rSLDS, inference_HMM, inference_ARHMM, filter_states_causal,

    # Regime-change detection
    cusum_overlay,

    # Evaluation (synthetic + actual data)
    evaluate_regimes_synthetic, evaluate_regimes_actual,

    # Bounds and diagnostics
    max_cpll_causal_bound, compute_stability_margin,

    # Parameter utilities
    print_rSLDS_matrices, get_rSLDS_params, compute_required_w,
)
```

## Key contributions over base ssm

- **Uniform fit API**: `fit_rSLDS`, `fit_HMM`, `fit_AR_HMM` all return the same
  `(xhat, zhat, elbo, q, mdl)` tuple so downstream code is model-agnostic.
- **Restricted EM** (`fit_rSLDS_restricted`): fits rSLDS with fixed-or-masked
  `C, d` emission matrices for interpretable, identification-constrained models.
- **Causal filters** (`inference_rSLDS` / `_HMM` / `_ARHMM`): strictly
  forward-only IMM / alpha-recursion filters. No look-ahead. Returns xhat,
  zhat, gamma, cpll, and a diagonal-Gaussian upper bound max_cpll.
- **CUSUM overlay** (`cusum_overlay`): SPRT-optimal regime-change detection
  on top of a fitted model. One threshold `h_z` (nats) governs changepoint
  sensitivity across all three model families.
- **Generic evaluators**: `evaluate_regimes_{synthetic,actual}` return label-
  invariant classification metrics, changepoint detection stats, stability
  margins, ELBO and CPLL diagnostics. No trading or domain assumptions.

